 vermitteln. Das Lehrbuch richtet sich explizit an Studierende der Romanistik sowie der großen romanischen Einzelphilologien (Frz., It., Span.).  aThis book provides a novel introduction to the theories and methods of Romance linguistics. Seven units trace the development of Romance linguistics up to the present day. The presentation is organized along the lines of different theories, questions, and methods. This book is intended for undergraduate students in Romance languages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLinguistics. 0aRomance languages. 0aRomance philology. 4aBachelor-Einführung. 4aLehrwerke. 4aRomanische Sprachwissenschaft. 4aRomanistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aRomance Linguistics.  aUndergraduate Introduction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK 2013z9783110317237oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978311028252840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030989840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110309898423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110309898/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2013